\pard\qc\b\fs34 1. INTRODUCTION\par
\pard\qj\fs24 The digital transformation of education, business, and public services has significantly increased demand for robust web applications. Django, a high-level Python web framework, is widely adopted for secure and scalable backend development. This training was designed to provide practical skills in developing production-ready web applications with clean architecture and maintainable code practices.\par
\par
The training followed a step-by-step progression from basic Python concepts to complete Django project implementation. Each topic included conceptual learning, live coding sessions, assignments, and project-based outcomes.\par
\page

\pard\qc\b\fs34 2. TRAINING OBJECTIVES\par
\pard\qj\fs24 The major objectives of this training were:\par
\pard\li720\qj - Build a strong foundation in Python for backend development.\par
- Understand Django project structure and MVT architecture.\par
- Develop database-driven web applications with CRUD features.\par
- Implement authentication, role-based access, and secure sessions.\par
- Build and consume REST APIs for modern web integrations.\par
- Apply testing, debugging, and security best practices.\par
- Deploy applications to production environments.\par
\pard\qj\li0 These objectives were successfully integrated into practical modules and project work.\par
\page

\pard\qc\b\fs34 3. INSTITUTE AND ASSET PROJECT CONTEXT\par
\pard\qj\fs24 This training was conducted under the academic and professional guidance framework of the institute and aligned with ASSET Project goals for skill development, employability enhancement, and practical ICT competence. The learning design emphasized industry alignment, project-based implementation, and measurable outcomes.\par
\par
The report template includes visual placeholders for both institute and ASSET logos on the cover page to support official documentation standards.\par
\page

\pard\qc\b\fs34 4. TRAINING METHODOLOGY\par
\pard\qj\fs24 The methodology combined theory, practice, and evaluation through:\par
\pard\li720\qj - Instructor-led sessions with demonstrations\par
- Guided lab exercises and coding tasks\par
- Daily recap and Q/A discussions\par
- Individual assignments and peer reviews\par
